dct_description_sm: New Jersey. Department of Conservation and Economic Development. Division of Planning and Development. Atlas Sheet 34 (1956) New Jersey Geological Survey. Alternate title: [New Jersey.] Atlas sheet no. 34. Relief show by 10 ft. contour interval and spot heights. Depth shown by 10 ft. contour interval at mean low tide. Original survey made under direction of C. C. Vermeule, Topographer in 1880-3, 1956 revision by R. G. Blanchard, Topographic Engineer. Title is not given. Region covered: southern Salem County and western Cumberland County.Title is not given. Region covered: southern Salem County and western Cumberland County.
dct_publisher_sm: Trenton, N.J. : New Jersey Geological Survey, 1956.
